content:
Dashboards help you visually understand changing business conditions so you can make decisions based on the real-time data you’ve gathered with reports. Use dashboards to help users identify trends, sort out quantities, and measure the impact of their activities.

Reports provide all the data shown in a dashboard. Dashboards can show data from more than one report. When refreshing a dashboard, all the data-providing reports must run.

Dashboards are shared via folders. Whomever has permission to the folder your dashboard is saved in also has access to your dashboard. Ensure that you save your dashboard in an appropriate folder.

The Dashboard Editor is a visual, drag-and-drop tool, which you use to create dashboards and edit existing ones. Dashboards are made up of widgets. Each widget contains a chart or metric that shows data from one report.

A dashboard only displays data that the dashboard’s running user can access. For example, if Emily is the dashboard’s running user, then the dashboard shows data about all the Leads in Salesforce. If Marcus is the running user, then the dashboard only shows data about Leads that Marcus owns.

Build a dashboard to share Salesforce data with colleagues. Dashboards let you curate data from reports using charts, tables, and metrics.

Filtering rules apply to fields from the dashboard’s source reports. After filters are defined, a user viewing the dashboard can select a filter to visualize the data of most interest.

You can control which data is visible based on the running user. Set up automatic dashboard refreshes and receive refreshed dashboard results by email on a schedule that you set.

Click a dashboard’s name to run it. Dashboard charts are interactive, so hover and click them to get more information.

If you’re not seeing the data that you expect, refresh for the latest data, check that you have the right running user, and verify your dashboard data sources.

To speed up sluggish dashboards, optimize source reports and plan dashboard refreshes. Dashboard refresh times can vary based on available resources.
title: Salesforce Dashboard Best Practices
